docs/20260402-cypherclaw-embodiment-prd.md:13:CypherClaw currently operates as a headless generative art system. It produces beautiful work, but it has no presence. A visitor encounters monitors displaying art but has no sense of meeting *something*. There is no face, no voice, no way to speak back. The system generates but does not converse. It observes but does not acknowledge.
docs/20260402-cypherclaw-embodiment-prd.md:99:- **Sensor connected:** Detected via udev/USB events. Registered in SenseWeave. Begins contributing to generation within one cycle.
docs/20260402-cypherclaw-embodiment-prd.md:109:- **Content:** GlyphWeave-generated ASCII/emoji face that evolves over time. Reflects the current narrative phase mood. Responds to sensory input in real time. Displays typed text from the mechanical keyboard — large, legible, immediate.
