docs/coherence-foundations.md:23:**Infrastructure-level enforcement is required.** Constitutional AI (Bai et al., 2022) showed that embedding constraints into the generation pipeline --- not just the prompt --- produces measurably more aligned outputs. PromptClaw extends this principle to the multi-agent case: the `CoherenceEngine` sits between the orchestrator and every agent invocation, injecting context, evaluating outputs, and blocking violations before they propagate.
docs/coherence-foundations.md:40:- **Cross-agent review (multi-agent debate).** Du et al. (ICML 2024) showed that having agents critique each other's outputs catches errors that self-review misses. The "debate" pattern --- where agents must justify their outputs to a reviewer --- produces higher accuracy than single-agent generation with planning.
