sdp/runner.log:11255:{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:04:50.842Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777698290484_0","status":"success","output":"commit a76dfd1ccd99bffd1c56dcf764adc7656c86f61d\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Fri May 1 21:43:59 2026 -0700\n\n    fix(scripts): align narrative smoke CLI with /health + X-Narrative-Auth [T-016@20260502T001347Za]\n    \n    Update scripts/smoke_narrative.py to probe the actual narrative_api\n    endpoint (/health) and send the operator token through the\n    X-Narrative-Auth header that cypherclaw.narrative_api enforces. The\n    prior /healthz + /readyz + Authorization: Bearer shape did not exist on\n    the target service, so the smoke run could never succeed against a\n    live API.\n    \n    Document the script in README.md and add a CHANGELOG entry so the\n    Deniable operator can validate from their Mac. Tests in\n    tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py now pin the /health endpoint and\n    the X-Narrative-Auth header propagation.\n\ndiff --git a/CHANGELOG.md b/CHANGELOG.md\nindex 1025890..3ddda31 100644\n--- a/CHANGELOG.md\n+++ b/CHANGELOG.md\n@@ -2,6 +2,8 @@\n \n ## Unreleased\n \n+- Added a stdlib-only narrative API smoke CLI (T-016@20260502T001347Za): `scripts/smoke_narrative.py` reads the base URL from `--base-url` or `NARRATIVE_BASE_URL` (defaulting to `http://cypherclaw:8765`), performs `GET /health` against `cypherclaw.narrative_api`, prints status code plus a 200-char body preview, and exits non-zero on any non-2xx response or connection failure. The optional `--token` flag is sent as the `X-Narrative-Auth` shared-secret header that the API enforces when `NARRATIVE_AUTH_TOKEN` is set, so the Deniable operator can validate the service from their Mac over Tailscale without a virtualenv. Documented in `README.md`; regression coverage in `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` pins the success path, non-2xx exit, unreachable-host exit, header propagation, and body truncation.\n+\n - Added depth-2 EMSD catalog helpers (frac-0001): `my-claw/curriculum/catalog.py` now exposes grouped category lookup, semester filtering, prerequisite graph output, stable exercise indexing, compact summary statistics, and catalog consistency validation. The helpers are pure, typed, and keep the existing 40-course catalog/scaffold contract unchanged; `tests/test_emsd_catalog_depth.py` pins meaningful helper output and validation error reporting.\n \n - Added the CypherClaw narrative entity mutation endpoint (T-015@20260502T001347Z): `PATCH /world/entities/{entity_id}` now accepts either a wrapped `{\"mutations\": [...]}` body or a single integration-spec `StateMutation` object, applies `set`, `increment`, `decrement`, `append`, and `remove` against entity `properties` paths, validates optional `target_entity` against the path ID, and persists the updated entity through duck-typed deploy-side store methods (`update_entity`/`patch_entity`/`save_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`record_entity`). The route returns the updated `EntityRecord`, surfaces missing entities as `404`, missing stores as `503`, validation failures as `422`, and downstream persistence failures as `502`. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the fighter `current_state` healthy-to-wounded round trip, numeric/list/nested mutation semantics, single-mutation payload compatibility, invalid-mutation no-persist behavior, missing entity/store handling, downstream failure handling, and shared-secret auth behavior.\n\ncommit 63ac8ae3aa02774f2d5e3cf105e4d32d5489d029\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Fri May 1 21:29:16 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(catalog): deepen curriculum helpers [frac-0001]\n\ndiff --git a/CHANGELOG.md b/CHANGELOG.md\nindex b81a683..1025890 100644\n--- a/CHANGELOG.md\n+++ b/CHANGELOG.md\n@@ -2,6 +2,8 @@\n \n ## Unreleased\n \n+- Added depth-2 EMSD catalog helpers (frac-0001): `my-claw/curriculum/catalog.py` now exposes grouped ca