rmalization pipeline so the new entity is immediately re-fetchable via `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}`, falls back to the request input for `type`/`name`/`domain`/`properties` when the store returns a partial record, and surfaces HTTP `502` when the store returns no ID, `503` when no store can be constructed, and `422` for whitelist/empty-string violations. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the squad-member round trip via GET, each whitelisted domain, blank/missing-input rejection, downstream-failure handling, missing-store fallback, partial-record fallback, no-ID surfacing, the record-dict signature path, and shared-secret auth behavior.\n\ncommit c9ab03ba958c91d2cbcec4b10258a4484e2cd32c\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Fri May 1 20:41:32 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(narrative-api): apply entity state mutations [T-015@20260502T001347Z]\n\ndiff --git a/CHANGELOG.md b/CHANGELOG.md\nindex 0abdd77..b81a683 100644\n--- a/CHANGELOG.md\n+++ b/CHANGELOG.md\n@@ -2,6 +2,8 @@\n \n ## Unreleased\n \n+- Added the CypherClaw narrative entity mutation endpoint (T-015@20260502T001347Z): `PATCH /world/entities/{entity_id}` now accepts either a wrapped `{\"mutations\": [...]}` body or a single integration-spec `StateMutation` object, applies `set`, `increment`, `decrement`, `append`, and `remove` against entity `properties` paths, validates optional `target_entity` against the path ID, and persists the updated entity through duck-typed deploy-side store methods (`update_entity`/`patch_entity`/`save_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`record_entity`). The route returns the updated `EntityRecord`, surfaces missing entities as `404`, missing stores as `503`, validation failures as `422`, and downstream persistence failures as `502`. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the fighter `current_state` healthy-to-wounded round trip, numeric/list/nested mutation semantics, single-mutation payload compatibility, invalid-mutation no-persist behavior, missing entity/store handling, downstream failure handling, and shared-secret auth behavior.\n+\n - Added the CypherClaw narrative entity creation endpoint (T-014@20260502T001347Z): `POST /world/entities` now accepts `{type, name, domain, properties}`, validates `domain` against the `{shared, cypherclaw, deniable}` whitelist before touching the store, and routes through a new `create_world_entity(...)` helper that duck-types the deploy-side world store across `create_entity`/`add_entity`/`record_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`save_entity` (kwarg-shaped or single-mapping signatures). The route returns HTTP `201` with the store-assigned ID populated through the shared entity normalization pipeline so the new entity is immediately re-fetchable via `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}`, falls back to the request input for `type`/`name`/`domain`/`properties` when the store returns a partial record, and surfaces HTTP `502` when the store returns no ID, `503` when no store can be constructed, and `422` for whitelist/empty-string violations. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the squad-member round trip via GET, each whitelisted domain, blank/missing-input rejection, downstream-failure handling, missing-store fallback, partial-record fallback, no-ID surfacing, the record-dict signature path, and shared-secret auth behavior.\n \n - Added the CypherClaw narrative beat endpoint (T-011@20260502T001347Z): `POST /beats/next` now validates `{cycle_number, domain_filter, arc_position_target?, force_arc_event?}`, wraps an injected or lazily imported deploy-side `NarrativeEngine.next_beat()`, preserves the engine-owned serialized `StoryBeat` JSON shape without padding absent fields, and returns clear `503` unavailable / `502` generation-failure errors. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_beats.py` pins parameter passing, raw mapping shape preservation, dataclass/nested serialization, validation-before-engine behavior, downstream failure handling, missing-engine fallback, and shared-secret auth behavior.\n\ncommit 2811e086b4e93369ab61f178d76232d842e1b7a3\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Fri May 1 20:10:08 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(narrative_api): implement POST /world/entities [T-014@20260502T001347Z]\n    \n    Adds entity creation endpoint at POST /world/entities accepting\n    {type, name, domain, properties} per PRD CN-008. Domain validated against\n    {shared, cypherclaw, deniable} whitelist before the store is touched. The\n    new create_world_entity() helper duck-types the deploy-side world store\n    across create_entity/add_entity/record_entity/upsert_entity/save_entity\n    (both kwarg-shaped and single-mapping signatures), normalizes the response\n    through the shared entity pipeline, and falls back to request input for\n    absent fields. Returns 201 on success, 422 on validation, 502 on\n    downstream failure or missing store-assigned id, and 503 when no store\n    can be constructed. Round-trip verified via GET /world/entities/{id}.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\ndiff --git a/CHANGELOG.md b/CHANGELOG.md\nindex 041bd71..0abdd77 100644\n--- a/CHANGELOG.md\n+++ b/CHANGELOG.md\n@@ -2,6 +2,8 @@\n \n ## Unreleased\n \n+- Added the CypherClaw narrative entity creation endpoint (T-014@20260502T001347Z): `POST /world/entities` now accepts `{type, name, domain, properties}`, validates `domain` against the `{shared, cypherclaw, deniable}` whitelist before touching the store, and routes through a new `create_world_entity(...)` helper that duck-types the deploy-side world store across `create_entity`/`add_entity`/`record_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`save_entity` (kwarg-shaped or single-mapping signatures). The route returns HTTP `201` with the store-assigned ID populated through the shared entity normalization pipeline so the new entity is immediately re-fetchable via `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}`, falls 